## Shared Pipeline: `_run_shared_fw_pipeline()`

> **Lines**: 1592–1833
> **Called by**: Both ✦ New Content AND ▶ Rewrite
> **Single source of truth** — sửa 1 chỗ = cả 2 pipeline đều update

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    O["Outline\ngenerate_renew_outline_v2()"] --> AU["Audit\naudit_outline()"]
    AU --> W["Write Chapters\nwrite_from_blueprint()\n(sequential, with prev_context)"]
    W --> R["Cross-chapter Review\nreview_narrative_full()"]
    R --> P{Auto-patch?}
    P -->|Yes| PA["patch_chapter_overlap()\n(critical/major only)"]
    P -->|No| M
    PA --> M["Merge → FULL_SCRIPT.txt"]
```

### Parameters

```python
_run_shared_fw_pipeline(
    fw_name,           # Framework name
    fw_output_dir,     # Where to save chapter files
    fw_pipeline_dir,   # Where to save pipeline artifacts
    fw_log,            # Logging function
    blueprint,         # Research data dict
    style_json_raw,    # Style JSON string
    endpoints,         # API endpoints list
    tier,              # "pro" or "flash"
    lang,              # "en" or "vi"
    niche,             # e.g. "biography tiểu sử nhân vật"
    stop_check,        # lambda: bool — cancellation
    get_wc_rule,       # fn(section) → "MIN-MAX words" or "SKIP"
    get_ch_range,      # fn() → "between 6 and 10 chapters"
    log_api=None,      # API call logger (Rewrite: actual, New Content: None)
    on_chapter_saved=None,  # Callback for Rewrite UI tracking
    auto_patch=True,   # Whether to auto-fix critical issues
)
```

### Step-by-step Detail

#### 1. Outline
- **Function**: `generate_renew_outline_v2(blueprint, style_json, fw_name, api, ...)`
- **Output**: `_renew_outline.json` with `{chapters: [...], narrative_arc: "..."}`
- **Each chapter**: `{title, chapter_type, key_points, estimated_word_count, ...}`

#### 2. Audit
- **Function**: `audit_outline(outline, blueprint, style_json, fw_name, api, ...)`
- **Tier**: Always Flash (fast + cheap)
- **Output**: `_audit.json` with issues found, `_renew_outline_audited.json` if fixed
- **Fixes**: Structural issues, missing coverage, chapter count violations

#### 3. Write Chapters
- **Function**: `write_from_blueprint(blueprint, style_json, fw_name, ch_outline, ...)`
- **Sequential**: Each chapter gets `prev_context` = last 2 chapters
- **Word count**: Per-section rules (open/body/end), `SKIP` = skip entirely
- **Chapter naming**: `ch_01_Title.txt` (type-aware: hook→Intro, end→Outro_CTA)
- **Error handling**: Failed chapters → empty string, pipeline continues

#### 4. Review + Patch
- **Function**: `review_narrative_full(rw_chapters, api, niche, lang, ...)`
- **Input**: List of `{filename, text, title}` dicts
- **Output**: `_review.json` with `{overall_flow_score, issues: [...]}`
- **Auto-patch**: For each critical/major issue:
  - `patch_chapter_overlap(chapter_text, issue, full_context, api)`
  - Overwrites both in-memory and file

#### 5. Merge
- **Output**: `FULL_SCRIPT.txt` with chapter headers and `====` separators
- **Format**:
  ```
  Chapter 1: Title
  
  [body text]
  
  ============================================================
  
  Chapter 2: Title
  
  [body text]
  ```

